## 2. Sensitive Personal Information (§ 1798.121)

[LEGAL REVIEW REQUIRED] — Sensitive PI retention is limited to what is
necessary for the purposes permitted under § 1798.121(a). Longer
retention requires consumer-facing disclosure plus a "Limit the Use of
My Sensitive Personal Information" link.

## 3. Deletion procedures

- Verifiable consumer deletion requests (§ 1798.105) are honoured within 45 days, extendable once by 45 days with notice.
- We instruct service providers and contractors that received the consumer's Personal Information to delete it from their records, unless an exception applies.
- We do not re-identify deidentified data once deletion has been actioned.

## 4. Statutory exceptions (§ 1798.105(d))

We may decline to delete to the extent retention is necessary to:

- Complete the transaction for which the Personal Information was collected.
- Detect security incidents or protect against malicious or illegal activity.
- Debug to identify and repair errors.
- Comply with a legal obligation (tax, employment, regulatory recordkeeping).
- Exercise free speech or another right provided for by law.

## 5. Backups and retention beyond the schedule

Data persisted in backups is purged on the next backup rotation cycle
after a deletion request, but is not used for any purpose other than
disaster recovery while it remains in backup.

## 6. Records

We maintain an internal log of deletion requests and their status for
at least 24 months per CCPA recordkeeping guidance.

## 7. Review

This policy is reviewed at least every 12 months as required by
§ 1798.130(a)(5).

